array([ 1., -1., nan])

I decided to add an example that demonstrates the behavior of the `sign` function with infinite and NaN inputs, as this is an important edge case that users may encounter. This example shows that the function returns 1 for positive infinity, -1 for negative infinity, and NaN for NaN inputs.

